The paper presents a motion planning algorithm, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses sampling-based techniques and optimization, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of graphs and trees, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
